reviews.text: Excellent Food, The Paneer and Tandoori Roti were here top class, highly suggested. The service was extremely good, very polite behaviour staff. Skyroof is a cozy rooftop caf√© and restaurant in Ujjain, offering a charming ambiance and an intimate vibe. My sister recently hosted a get-together here for 20 people. While the rooftop isn‚Äôt very spacious, it accommodates around 40-50 people, making it ideal for small gatherings.

The food left me with mixed feelings. The starters were excellent, bursting with flavor, and undoubtedly the highlight of the meal. However, the main course‚Äîvegetable dishes and dal‚Äîwas just average and didn‚Äôt quite match the expectations set by the starters.

The biggest drawback, unfortunately, was the service. It was noticeably slow, and the staff seemed inattentive despite multiple requests. This aspect could use significant improvement.

On the brighter side, the rooftop vibe was enjoyable and made the evening pleasant despite the slow service.
The hotel's food was excellent. From the fresh ingredients to the skillful preparation, each dish was a culinary delight
